text: Felicity Passon (born 11 July 1999) is a Seychellois swimmer. She competed in the women's 50 metre freestyle at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. She represented Seychelles at the 2019 African Games, winning two gold medals, one silver medal and one bronze medal, and qualified for the Tokyo 2020 Olympics. ==References== Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Seychellois female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Competitors at the 2019 African Games Category:African Games medalists in swimming Category:African Games gold medalists for Seychelles Category:African Games silver medalists for Seychelles Category:African Games bronze medalists for Seychelles Category:Female freestyle swimmers Category:African Games competitors for Seychelles
